content: As soon as <code class="language-python">index</code> equals <code class="language-python">20</code>, the body of the conditional construct (<code class="language-python">if</code>) is executed. The break statement stops the loop and the interpreter continues just after the <code class="language-python">while</code> body. Consider this piece of code just as an example, since it’s better to evaluate as much as possible into the <code class="language-python">while</code> condition.
